comments: Ball (CHI) reaches in and makes clean contact with the ball when he steals it from Gordon (HOU).
DeRozan (CHI) moves forward towards Wood (HOU) on the perimeter but the contact is marginal as he makes the pass.
Caruso (CHI) jumps vertically and maintains a legal vertical position contesting the driving shot attempt by Mathews (HOU).
Green (CHI) is the last player to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds.
Correctly called delay of game violation.
LaVine (CHI) lifts his pivot foot before the start of his dribble.
Ball (CHI) briefly clamps Gordon's (HOU) arm but releases and he is still able to grab the rebound.
LaVine (CHI) commits a take foul on House Jr. (HOU).
LaVine (CHI) makes clean contact with the ball during the steal prior to any incidental contact with Porter Jr. (HOU).
Ball (CHI) commits a take foul on Mathews (HOU).
